dataIdInfo.idPurp:
This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data.
[The purpose of this feature class is to provide a digital data source of tax parcels and their associated text annotation so as to depict as accurate a representation of land ownership as possible. Associated with each polygon feature is a unique attribute occurrence of the County Tax Parcel Identification Number (PIN). The PIN attribute is used to join to the County Tax Listing Department files. Joining to the Assessors tax table provides additional attributes for each parcel including owner's name, address, improved value, assessed acreage, etc.]
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This data layer represents parcels for Lincoln County, Wisconsin in 2007. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Lincoln_Parcels_2007.gdb. [The Lincoln County Land Information Office plans to maintain the cadastral features in a ESRI ArcGIS 9.0 personal geodatabase using the ArcMap COGO tools. The parcels are entered via coordinate geometry where legal descriptions allow. Source documents include assessor's plats, recorded subdivisions, CSMs, metes and bounds property descriptions obtained from the tax roll, state and county highway plans, plats or survey and sketches where no legal documents exist. Where coordinate geometry cannot be used to create the parcels, they are entered using the most accurate methods available. Parcel development is referenced to the Lincoln County Coordinate System and geographic control features. Methods for entry of parcels pertaining to condominium plats are reviewed on a case-by-case basis.]
